{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Cake","content":["Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and flour a springform pan (10 in.) and set aside.","Place bread into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>15 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add walnuts and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside.","Place flour and cloves into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>20 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer into bowl with bread-walnut mixture.","Place butter, eggs and sugar into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>2 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add reserved bread-walnut-flour mixture, cinnamon, baking powder, brandy and milk and mix <nobr>25 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer mixture to prepared springform pan and bake for 50-60 minutes (350°F). Allow cake to cool in pan. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl"]},{"title":"Syrup","content":["Place 3 oz sugar and lemon peel into mixing bowl and zest <nobr>30 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add remaining 15 oz sugar and water. Split vanilla pod lengthwise, scrape out seeds and add seeds and vanilla pod into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>9 min\/212°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Remove vanilla pod. Pour syrup over cooled walnut cake and wait until all the syrup is absorbed. Slice cake and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Cake","content":["2 ½ oz unsalted butter, plus extra to grease","6 oz all-purpose flour, plus extra to dust","2 oz stale bread, broken into pieces","9 oz walnut pieces","3 whole cloves","3 large eggs","4 ½ oz sugar","½ tsp ground cinnamon","1 tbsp baking powder","1 tbsp brandy","4 ½ oz milk"]},{"title":"Syrup","content":["18 oz sugar, divided","½ organic lemon, thin peel only, no pith","12 ½ oz water","1 vanilla bean pod"]}],"id":"r113839","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-0kWPX75NboY\/XZWp2lKBpKI\/AAAAAAAAfQE\/bZO2CElZpS8emA3BsGPK0uMTJRafA-GsgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7jkQsTF0A58ovViH.png","title":"Greek Walnut Cake 'Karidopita'","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"16 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"53 g","calories":"1516 kJ \/ 362 kcal"},"usefulItems":"springform pan (10 in.), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Greek walnut cake “Karidopita”: one of the most popular cakes in Greece made with walnuts and bread, giving a soft but crunchy texture in every bite. Its texture, thanks to soaking in sugar syrup, is surprisingly sponge-like.","Brandy can be replaced with prune juice, apple cider or simply water.","To optimize the absorption of syrup use a wooden skewer to evenly poke holes in the cake, allowing syrup to be more uniformly absorbed. Top cake with finely chopped walnuts to cover skewer holes."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 15m","16 slices"]}